Metadata Value: Covers 200 countries with data from 1962 to 2014. It has three main indicators: the Export Diversification Index, which can be disaggregated into sub-indices covering the Extensive Margin and the Intensive Margin. As these are Theil indices, higher values for all three correspond to lower export diversification.
Henn, C., C. Papageorgiou, N. Spatafora, 2013. “Export Quality in Developing Countries”, IMF Working Paper 13/108
